AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1024 House Bill No. 1036*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-201(f)(7)(B)(iii), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting instead:
(iii)
(a) Except as provided in subdivision (f)(7)(B)(iii)(b), meetings of the
state university boards must be made available for viewing by the public over the
internet by streaming video accessible from the respective institution's website.
Archived videos of the board meetings must also be available to the public
through the respective institution's website.
(b) Notwithstanding another law to the contrary, a state university board
of trustees may conduct private meetings to discuss or deliberate on matters
related to senior administration, personnel positions, and contracts; provided,
that a state university board of trustees shall not take action on matters related to
senior administration, personnel positions, and contracts in a private meeting.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
